/*
Ans-8

    <figure> tag
    1->   The figure tag is used to semantically organize the content of images, videos, audios or even charts or tables, block of codes in the HTML document.

    2->   <figure> tag is a container tag.

    3->   This tag provides a container for content that is equivalent to a figure or diagram in a book.

    4->   This tag is inline element.

    5->   It makes it easy for the machine to understand the code. Easy to get on search engines.

    6->   The figure tag contains default alignment and styling.


    <img> tag

    1->   The image tag is used to add an image to an   HTML page. <img> tag can only insert image.

    2->   <img> tag is a void tag.

    3->   The HTML <img> tag is used for embedding images into an HTML document.

    4->   It is an inline element but when we specify width and height it becomes a block element.

    5->   It is difficult for machines to understand.

    6->   The image tag does not contain any default alignment and styling.

    
*/